<HEADLINE> Indian Woman Is Miss Universe 2000  </HEADLINE>
By VIJAY JOSHI
<TEXT>
<P>
   NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) -- A 21-year-old model from India who said
beauty pageants give women a platform to ''voice our choices and
opinions'' was named Miss Universe early Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Lara Dutta succeeded Mpule Kwelagobe of Botswana to become the
49th winner of the pageant and the first Miss Universe of the new
millennium.
</P>
<P>
   ''It is going to take a while to sink in. It is a wonderful and
incredible, exhilarating feeling,'' Dutta said.
</P>
<P>
   Claudia Morena, 22, of Venezuela was second and Helen Lindes,
18, of Spain was third. Miss USA Lynnette Cole, 22, of Columbia,
Tenn., was among the five finalists.
</P>
<P>
   Dutta, who holds a master's degree in communications, won out
over 78 other contestants who had competed over the past three
weeks on this Mediterranean island, which promoted itself as the
island of love.
</P>
<P>
   The show was broadcast live on CBS television, beginning at 4
a.m. in Cyprus. Organizers said they chose that odd local hour to
take advantage of the prime time evening viewing in the Americas.
</P>
<P>
   Dutta won the crown after impressing the judges on the final
question of the contest: What would you say to those who condemn
the contest as an affront to women.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think pageants like Miss Universe give us young women a
platform to foray in the fields that we want to and forge ahead,''
Dutta said. ''It gives us a platform to voice our choices and
opinions.''
</P>
<P>
   The pageant was carried out amid a background of protest, with
the cypriot Church condemning it as being unchristian and an
affront to feminism.
</P>
<P>
   After sunset Friday, about 100 mostly middle-age women held an
all-night protest vigil at a hilltop church overlooking the
Eleftheria stadium where the pageant is being held.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier, the parishioners distributed leaflets on the street
that said: ''Shame to the beauty contest which plunges women down
to the bottomless pit of hell.''
</P>
<P>
   Cyprus' Westernized residents have largely ignored the church
protests, which also center on the pageant sponsors linking it to
Aphrodite, the Greek goddess of love.
</P>
<P>
   As her name was announced, Dutta, wearing a single-strap,
glittering red gown, raised her hand to her mouth and hugged
Moreno, of Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
   Dutta had consistently impressed the judges with her beauty,
poise and presence, winning the swimsuit event and placing fourth
the evening gown competition.
</P>
<P>
   ''She represents the women of 2000s so clearly,'' said
motivation speaker Tony Robbins, one of the judges. ''She had such
a regal aura about her.''
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   http://www.missuniverse.com
</P>
</TEXT>
