<HEADLINE> Athletics 9, Mariners 7  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Matt Stairs hit a three-run homer in the
ninth inning as the Oakland Athletics rallied from a five-run
deficit to beat the Seattle Mariners 9-7 on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   Oakland, which trailed 5-0 after three innings, was behind 7-6
entering the ninth. Pinch-hitter Terrence Long led off with a
single off Kazuhiro Sasaki (1-2) and moved to second on a sacrifice
bunt by Randy Velarde.
</P>
<P>
   Jason Giambi was intentionally walked setting up the
game-winning hit by Stairs, who got into the game when Olemdo Saenz
left in the second inning with a sprained left ankle.
</P>
<P>
   Stairs hit a 1-0 pitch over the fence in right-center for his
fifth home run. He threw his right hand in the air as he rounded
the bases.
</P>
<P>
   T.J. Mathews (2-2) got two outs for the win as Oakland moved
into sole possession of first place in the AL West this late in the
season for the first time since winning the division in 1992. The
A's lead Seattle by a half-game.
</P>
<P>
   Edgar Martinez hit a three-run homer and Alex Rodriguez drove in
three runs for Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   Ramon Hernandez hit a two-run homer for the A's.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing 6-5, Seattle took the lead with two runs in the
seventh. Carlos Guillen walked to lead off the inning advanced to
second on a wild pitch and third on a groundout with two outs.
</P>
<P>
   Rodriguez tied the game with an infield single off Jeff Tam.
John Olerud followed with an RBI double off Mike Magnante to give
Seattle the 7-6 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Oakland starter Omar Olivares allowed six runs on six hits and
four walks in six innings.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle starter John Halama allowed four runs, two hits and six
walks in four innings.
</P>
<P>
   Martinez gave the Mariners a 5-0 lead in the third with his
eighth home run of the season, a three-run shot off Olivares.
Rodriguez also doubled home a run in the inning.
</P>
<P>
   Jeremy Giambi doubled home a run in the fourth, the A's scored
three runs on one hit in the fifth.
</P>
<P>
   Halama gave up four walks and hit a batter to the first five
hitters of the inning. Velarde and Jason Giambi each walked with
the bases loaded. Ben Grieve also drove in a run with a single.
</P>
<P>
Notes: John Mabry was activated from the 15-day DL before the
game. ... Catcher Joe Oliver was optioned to Triple-A Tacoma. ...
Martinez extended his hitting streak to 11 games with a single in
the first inning. ... Olivares has allowed three home runs in his
last two starts after allowing one in his first six.
</P>
</TEXT>
