<HEADLINE> Gunmen Free 150 Brazil Jail Inmates  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) -- Eight heavily armed men stormed a jail
in South America's most populous city Saturday and freed nearly 150
inmates, police said.
</P>
<P>
   ''The gunmen barged in firing machine guns and revolvers,'' said
Domingos Paulo Neto, head of the police precinct in Cidade Dutra, a
low-income district on the outskirts of Sao Paulo, where about 16
million people live.
</P>
<P>
   A police officer was wounded in both legs and a prison guard was
hit in the head with a pistol, Paulo Neto said.
</P>
<P>
   Paulo Neto said the gunmen freed 144 inmates, 19 of whom have
been recaptured. Eight prisoners in a maximum security cell were
the only ones who did not escape.
</P>
<P>
   Most of the prisoners were being held on charges of robbery and
drug trafficking. Others were charged with rape and murder.
</P>
