<HEADLINE> Cast of 'Friends' Has Deadline  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Will television viewers lose their
''Friends?''
</P>
<P>
   Cast members of the popular NBC sitcom have until noon Sunday to
resolve their salary dispute with Warner Bros., the studio that
produces the show, or get booted from the network's fall lineup.
</P>
<P>
   The six principal cast members have demanded $1 million per
episode.
</P>
<P>
   Warner Bros. would not comment Saturday, but reportedly has
offered each actor $800,000 per episode for 22 shows. NBC
spokeswoman Shirley Powell would not comment on the specifics of
the salary negotiations, but said the deadline applied to ''all
parties'' in the negotiations.
</P>
<P>
   ''Either 'Friends' will be in the lineup Monday or not,'' she
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The network unveils its fall schedule Monday in New York.
</P>
<P>
   The top-rated series starring Jennifer Aniston, Courteney Cox
Arquette, Lisa Kudrow, Matt LeBlanc, Matthew Perry and David
Schwimmer has appeared on NBC for six seasons.
</P>
<P>
   Each actor reportedly earned $125,000 per episode this season.
</P>
