<HEADLINE> Admirals Defeat Thunder 24-21  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) -- Ron Powlus hit LC Stevens on a
34-yard touchdown pass with 3:28 remaining in overtime Saturday and
the Amsterdam Admirals scored their second NFL Europe overtime win
this season, defeating the Berlin Thunder 24-21.
</P>
<P>
   Thunder kicker Jaret Holmes was true from 49 yards after
regulation ended 18-18, but NFL Europe League rules allow each team
an overtime possession. Powlus then connected with Stevens to give
Amsterdam a 3-2 and a share of second place with the Scottish
Claymores.
