<HEADLINE> AM-CT-BRF--Student Dies, 1st Ld-Writethru, 142  </HEADLINE>
Man sentenced in Trinity College beating death   
sdjchfcsd
<TEXT>
<P>
   HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- A 20-year-old Hartford man has been
sentenced to 2 1/2 years in prison for a beating that resulted in
the death of a Trinity College freshman last fall.
</P>
<P>
   Alfredo Galvez was sentenced Friday in Hartford Superior Court.
He had entered a plea to 2nd degree manslaughter under the Alfred
doctrine, which means he did not admit guilt but conceded the state
had enough evidence to win a conviction.
</P>
<P>
   Herme ''John'' Ortiz, 17. of the Bronx, N.Y., died a week after
the fight last September at a campus party.
</P>
<P>
   Galvez punched Ortiz twice in the face after an argument,
witnesses said. Ortiz fell, hitting his head on the sidewalk.
</P>
<P>
   Galvez was an invited guest on campus, but not a Trinity
student, college officials said.
</P>
