<HEADLINE> Long Shot Out Of Mind Wins Race  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Long shot Out Of Mind and Eddie
Delahoussaye broke slowly but worked quickly in deep stretch to win
the $150,000 Mervyn LeRoy Handicap by a half length Saturday at
Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   Early Pioneer, with Matt Garcia, finished second, 4{ lengths in
front of Skimming and Victor Espinoza in a field of seven in the
Grade II handicap for 3-year-olds and up. Laffit Pincay Jr. rode
favorite Puerto Madero, a 6-year-old bay carrying high weight 120
pounds, for seventh place. Puerto Madero had 11 wins in 23 starts
with earnings of $1.3 million but hasn't won in 16 months.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't know what's wrong with him,'' Pincay said. ''He broke
good and I figured I'd be laying close. We went into the first turn
and he wanted to back off.''
</P>
<P>
   Out Of Mind, a 5-year-old bay and stablemate of Chilean-bred
Puerto Madero, covered 1 1/16 miles on a track rated fast in 1:41
4-5, winning $90,000 for career earnings of $180,313 in 12 starts.
The 13-1 shot paid $28.40, $10.20 and $7.20.
</P>
<P>
   Out of the gate in last place, Brazilian-bred Out Of Mind
settled off the rail and made a sharp move forward on the second
turn.
</P>
<P>
   Delahoussaye also won at Santa Anita aboard Out Of Mind.
</P>
<P>
   ''The day I won on him, I let him settle and just made one
run,'' Delahoussaye said. ''He proved he liked it that way better
than running early. I thought I moved too soon today. I moved at
the three-eighths pole. I should have waited for the quarter pole
and I'd have won easily.''
</P>
</TEXT>
