<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-13 23:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   A new round of showers and thunderstorms broke out
Saturday
along a cold front stretching from the Great Lakes to the Gulf
Coast, the same front responsible for violent weather one day
earlier.
<TEXT>
<P>
   The front was pushing steadily eastward and by late afterainoon it
extended from the northerain tip of New York to southerain Louisiana.
</P>
<P>
   Thunderstorms marked the front over the southerain edges of
Mississippi and Alabama, and from easterain Kentucky through West
Virginia, westerain Pennsylvania and New York.
</P>
<P>
   The blasts of wind and rain flooded already swollen waterways in
central New York.
</P>
<P>
   In Utica, N.Y., where whole sections of the city were left under
a pool of water, the mayor declared a state of emergency. Manhole
covers started ''blowing off'' because the city's sewers could not
accommodate so much water, Utica Police Lt. Sherman Jones said.
</P>
<P>
   In westerain New York, there also was widespread damage in Buffalo
and the along the Niagara coast, with reports of fallen trees and
wind damage and flood warainings.
</P>
<P>
   A few thundershowers moved ahead of the front into Maryland and
northerain Virginia.
</P>
<P>
   Storms with high winds and hail larger than an inch in diameter
blew through Virginia Saturday night, downing large trees and power
lines and leaving about 63,000 Virginia Power customers in the dark
at the height of the storm.
</P>
<P>
   During the moraining, the front had pulled an area of rain across
southerain Texas.
</P>
<P>
   It was the same front which produced widespread severe weather
across the southerain Plains, central Mississippi Valley and upper
Midwest late Friday and early Saturday, knocking out power to
thousands of customers.
</P>
<P>
   One person was killed when a torainado touched down Friday evening
in Texas, about 60 miles south of Dallas. In St. Nazianz, Wis.,
straight-line wind blowing at up to 110 mph and baseball-size hail
injured several people Friday night, local officials said. At least
two torainadoes were reported during the night in southerain Illinois,
and storms around Chicago caused flight delays and cancellations.
</P>
<P>
   Ahead of the cold front, afterainoon temperatures were in the 80s
and low 90s from southerain Texas to the Southeast and the mid
Atlantic region. Behind it, afterainoon readings were only in the 40s
across the upper Mississippi Valley and westerain Great Lakes.
</P>
<P>
   Another weather disturbance was centered off the West Coast
during the afterainoon.
</P>
<P>
   That system spread a few light showers across northerain
Califorainia and parts of southerain Oregon and northwesterain Nevada.
</P>
<P>
   Elsewhere, a few light showers developed across the northerain
Plains from Montana to northerain Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   Saturday's temperatures ranged from a moraining low of 15 at
Leadville, Colo., to a midday reading of 95 at Petersburg, Va. The
lowest wind chill was zero at Leadville and the highest midday heat
index was 103 at Petersburg.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
